The paper discusses challenges and methods related to federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses distributed optimization and privacy-preserving data analysis, which are relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) respectively. The paper also mentions the potential use of federated learning in various applications, such as healthcare and autonomous systems, which are relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) respectively.
